The paper proposes a machine learning algorithm for function approximation using a multiobjective genetic programming framework. The algorithm involves creating a heterogeneous flexible neural tree and using an ensemble system to improve performance. This work falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), neural networks (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data mining (cs.DM), and systems and control (cs.SY).
